00:00:31.390 --> 00:00:32.770
Number 1:

00:00:32.770 --> 00:00:38.939
People who speak two or more languages may change their personalities between languages without even knowing it

00:00:39.399 --> 00:00:44.819
So someone may become more introverted when speaking French, or more agreeable when speaking German

00:00:46.030 --> 00:00:47.530
Number 2:

00:00:47.530 --> 00:00:55.440
People are more likely to follow orders in unfamiliar settings. This is because we're more likely to be obedient when we're unsure

00:00:55.989 --> 00:00:58.259
or when we feel others have more knowledge than us

00:00:59.050 --> 00:01:04.710
So if you want someone to do something with you, like go on a trip, maybe ask them in an unfamiliar environment

00:01:06.580 --> 00:01:13.199
Number 3: Even those who are concerned with equality, holds implicit bias about things such as race

00:01:13.900 --> 00:01:21.209
This is due to something known as the out-group bias, where we implicitly trust those who aren't a part of our in-group plus

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:24.629
It is important to remember that this is implicit?

00:01:25.299 --> 00:01:27.299
Meaning it is not consciously controlled

00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:30.720
Number 4:

00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:33.209
Eye contact makes us more resistant to persuasion

00:01:34.150 --> 00:01:41.549
This seems to be because eye contact is related to dominance- something we resent when someone is trying to persuade us to change our minds

00:01:42.399 --> 00:01:46.799
so when you're trying to convince someone to buy something or to go to the cinema with you,

00:01:47.470 --> 00:01:49.470
eye contact might not be good

00:01:50.500 --> 00:01:51.880
Number 5:

00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:57.509
The actor-observer bias is a tendency for us to blame our behavior on situational factors

00:01:57.759 --> 00:02:01.229
But blame other people's behaviors on internal factors

00:02:01.799 --> 00:02:05.688
For example, we may blame our own bad mood on getting stuck in traffic

00:02:06.200 --> 00:02:09.019
Why we would blame others bad mood on the personality

00:02:09.929 --> 00:02:12.589
It's important we don't just make exceptions for ourselves

00:02:12.959 --> 00:02:17.569
So try to be open-minded towards others when working out why they haven't acted a certain way

